availability.p: For internal use by the Faclair na Gàidhlig/DASG projects

note.p: The letter preceding the d is strange and appeas to have been an i which was then changed to somehting else. The present editor thinks it is meant to represent an a.
Is the first letter here an i or what?
I don't know whether this is just Mac Pháill's erratic spacing or if the 'as' + potential superscript 'i' is supposed to be an insert into the following MS line
The lenition marker is placed over the final t in this word but has been transcribed as belonging to the c and the -cht to indicate pre-aspiration.
